    <title>Scholarship Program Seeks to Boost Students Earning Financial Planning Degrees</title>
    <link>https://www.collegeboard.org/membership/all-access/financial-aid-academic/scholarship-program-seeks-boost-students-earning</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-image field-type-image field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; rel=&quot;&quot; resource=&quot;https://www.collegeboard.org/sites/default/files/styles/all_access_image_style/public/scholars%20outside%20NSE.JPG?itok=PjQSW0L3&quot;&gt;&lt;img typeof=&quot;foaf:Image&quot; src=&quot;https://www.collegeboard.org/sites/default/files/styles/all_access_image_style/public/scholars%20outside%20NSE.JPG?itok=PjQSW0L3&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-author field-type-text field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;Michael Preston, Associate Director of Communications&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-newsletter-tags field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/all-access-tags/td-ameritrade&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;TD Ameritrade&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/all-access-tags/financial-planning&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;financial planning&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/all-access-tags/temple-university&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;Temple University&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/all-access-tags/university-north-texas&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;University of North Texas&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/all-access-tags/nextgen-financial-planning-scholarship&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;NextGen Financial Planning Scholarship&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Students looking to build a career focused on helping people better manage and understand their finances have a new scholarship opportunity available to help them reach their goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.tdainstitutional.com/lp/nextgen-scholarship.page&quot;&gt;The TD Ameritrade Institutional NextGen Financial Planning Scholarship and Grant Program&lt;/a&gt; offers students a $5,000 one-time, non-renewable award that can be used to pursue a career in the financial planning industry. Open to current college freshmen, sophomores and juniors who are pursuing financial planning degrees at accredited four-year colleges or universities, the scholarships are awarded based on academic merit and a students’ passion for the subject. Award funds can be applied to tuition, fees, books and supplies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since launching in 2013, the program has given out 34 scholarships. This year, two new scholarship awards were created in an effort to attract more African-American, Hispanic, Native American and female students to careers in the industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the student scholarships, there is a related grant program that provides funding to institutions of higher education to help them launch or expand financial planning degree programs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This year, two universities – Temple and the University of North Texas – were  awarded grants under the program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cindy Axelrod, Director of Financial Planning Programs at Temple’s Fox School of Business in Philadelphia, said the $25,000 emerging-program grant awarded to her institution will be used to create a new undergraduate degree in financial planning that will help graduates fill a growing need in the local economy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“The expected job growth for financial planning is tremendous and the market need is tremendous,” she said. “Our new financial planning major will allow our graduates to emerge ready for a career that has a promising future. There’s an enormous inter-generational wealth transfer that will place the next several years and people need help deciding how to invest their money.”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the new major, Temple will also use a portion of the grant money to start a student chapter of the Financial Planning Association, a national organization that helps students network and learn more about careers in the industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the University of North Texas in Dallas, a $50,000 grant award for an established program will be used to both broaden the scope of the current financial degree program and increase the number of students in the major.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“We pursued this grant to not only improve our existing program and provide more job-ready students for advisors, but also to help improve the education of future advisors across the nation,” said David Ragan, an adjunct faculty member.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The grant will also help fund paid internships for financial planning majors at the University of North Texas’ Student Money Management Center, an award-winning program that provides planning services to students and faculty members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Like Temple’s Axelrod, Ragan sees a wealth of career opportunities available for students who pursue degrees in financial planning.  According to statistics from the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics, the industry needs, on average, about 6,300 new advisors to enter the field annually to keep up with demand through 2022. But in 2014, just over 3,200 people passed the Certified Financial Planner exam.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“It comes down to supply and demand,” he said.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Students and institutions interested in the TD Ameritrade Institutional NextGen Financial Planning Scholarship and Grant Program are encouraged to find out more in advance of next year’s application period &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.tdainstitutional.com/lp/nextgen-scholarship.page&quot;&gt;at the TD Ameritrade website.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span property=&quot;dc:title&quot; content=&quot;Scholarship Program Seeks to Boost Students Earning Financial Planning Degrees&quot; class=&quot;rdf-meta element-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;</description>
